\par\plain \f0\fs28\b0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 - The town is an allegory for several things, including:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 1) itself;}
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 2) my own philosophy;}
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 3) The Institute (its diametric opposite).}
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 - It is a community that has moved from an \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93elevated\u8221\'94 state to a base state. Its absurdity contains a kind of honesty, in its adherence to literalist, dogmatic materialism.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 - Unlike the reference in the }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "scrivlnk://87303DB0-DC77-45A3-B26D-0274E1058E99"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 Kindle piece}}{\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 , its placement is entirely accidental, if symbolic. It sits on the great river, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93That Whose Name We Do Not Know\u8221\'94, which filters ideas and ideology, like all valleys, but in a far more literal way. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 - They are most definitely NOT aliens. There have been plenty of hints that way so far. They are a society learning how to exist. They have }{\f0\fs28\b0\ul\ulc0\cf1 not}{\f0\fs28\b0\cf1  been there long. Embarrassment at knowing each other. Very few of them live together. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 - They damn imported goods - people come and leave it in the valley. They are ideal to be the focus of a charity. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 - They are like as children.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 - It is a mystery as to how it can support itself. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 - They find it odd that humans group together for comfort - stand in groups, the \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93barbeque philosophy\u8221\'94. Especially families, fathers and sons.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 - Their \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93information society\u8221\'94 is broken. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 - The town is, in a way, a stage for the Eremite; he is presented with a very limited view of life there, despite his best efforts to be omnipresent and act as its surrogate deity. Is there a way for the audience to be aware of what is kept, as it were, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93backstage\u8221\'94 from him? This would obviously integrate into the OC initially, but would then be applicable to missing portions of the MC, and also the reader\u8217\'92s understanding.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 - They are decaying into mongoloids, having accepted the disease. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 - It is an interesting question as to why they would live here - surely they could make a choice to live somewhere else? Outside of the valley? }
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 - The town stands for febrility biology and the fall of all ascension into mundanity and bodily needs.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 - There has to be a breach in the valley\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s wall of silence. How does information get in and out? }
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\cf1 - The town is }{\f2\fs28\b0\i1\cf1 meant }{\f0\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 to be a demonstration of how to progress society without changing it fundamentally.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 - The Execution Venn provides an interesting philosophical problem. One can choose to die without guilt or incrimination, and others can choose for themselves which category into which they will fit. }
