\par\plain {\f1\fs36\b1\i0\cf1 Water}
\par\plain \f0\fs28\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 - Fermentation vs. Distillation; the townsfolk are terrified of ideas sticking. However, given the \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93stickiness\u8221\'94 of existence, this is impossible to avoid. The valley invites water to stay. Gravity is both their ally and hated foe, being what brought them from the heavens, but which also helps them }{\f2\fs28\b0\i1\cf1 move }{\f0\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 water. Water, funnily, would be the only thing that could wash away the \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93ideas\u8221\'94 of which they speak. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 - The sea is a move to ascension, back to their past, and this is why they hate it. It also resembles Loss in information. But that information can be in the air around, and in fact becomes so. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 - Ritual is linked to cooking, fecundity, the earth and body.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 - They do not wash, and this leads them to believe that rot drives away the gods, when in fact it attracts them. Water in the earth needs to be dried out, and nobody is buried.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 - We are pushed from the center as we get older, to die - this is why they hate the sea - ends up in an old folk\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s home by the sea - did not die, as they said?}
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 - They are even scared of the fluids in their bodies. They never wash, and the distribution of water (for example, in the canals) is tightly controlled. They love the sound of it, but cannot attach it to the physical thing that they hate (when heard in isolation).}
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 - They are called Loss because something is lost by their interference in the stream of information. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 - Dams are the interpretation of a river. Battle with them over generations. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 - They never take their clothes off - they are the clothes that they were found in}
